{
  "text": "and SlMC6 in tomato metacaspase gene family. Similarly, type II metacaspases, SotubMC7 and SotubMC8 showed significant similarity in their gene structure visa-vis their tomato counterparts, SlMC7 and SlMC8, respectively [CITATION_1] . The gene structure analysis so performed supports the classification of potato metacaspases. Furthermore, the significant similarity between the predicted structures of SotubMCs belonging to the same class provides an additional supporting data for their classification.",
